&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Guinness World Records&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Originally founded by the Guinness Brewery in 1955, it has become the primary international authority on the cataloging and verification of world records in various fields of human achievement and natural wonders.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

questions.statement:
Consider the following statements regarding the newly approved Small Hydro Power Development Scheme:&lt;br /&gt;
I: The scheme supports Small Hydro Power projects with a capacity ranging exclusively between 1 Megawatt and 25 Megawatts.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
II: For North Eastern States, Central Financial Assistance is provided at ₹2.4 Crore Per Megawatt.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
III: The scheme has been sanctioned with a total budget of ₹2,584.60 crores for the period from 2026-27 to 2030-31.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Which of the statements given above are correct?

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Only I and III.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Union Cabinet has approved the Small Hydro Power Development Scheme for the period of Fiscal Year 2026-27 to Fiscal Year 2030-31 to boost renewable energy infrastructure.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statement I is correct:&lt;/strong&gt; The scheme specifically supports the installation of Small Hydro Power projects with a capacity ranging between 1 Megawatt and 25 Megawatts.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statement II is incorrect:&lt;/strong&gt; In the North Eastern States and districts with international borders, Central Financial Assistance is provided at &lt;strong&gt;₹3.6 Crore Per Megawatt&lt;/strong&gt; (capped at ₹30 Crores). The ₹2.4 Crore Per Megawatt rate applies to all other states.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statement III is correct:&lt;/strong&gt; The scheme has been officially sanctioned with a total budget of ₹2,584.60 Crores for the operational period from Fiscal Year 2026-27 to 2030-31.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Small Hydro Power Scheme Facts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Target Capacity - 1,500 Megawatts&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Total Investment Catalyst - ₹15,000 Crores&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Job Creation - 51 Lakh Person Days&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Atmanirbhar Bharat Alignment&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Overview: The investment will leverage 100 percent of plant and machinery from indigenous sources, promoting self-reliance in the renewable energy sector.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Environmental Advantages&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Overview: These projects are decentralized and environmentally sustainable as they avoid large-scale land acquisition, deforestation, and community displacement.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Transmission Efficiency&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Overview: Due to their decentralized nature, the need for long transmission lines is minimal, which significantly reduces Transmission Losses across the power grid.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rs 1.5 Crore.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ministry of Health and Family Welfare has approved major reforms to FSSAI regulations to enhance the Ease of Doing Business.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Turnover Revision:&lt;/strong&gt; The threshold for &lt;strong&gt;Basic Registration&lt;/strong&gt; has been significantly raised from Rs 12 Lakh to &lt;strong&gt;Rs 1.5 Crore&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Licensing Categories:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;State Licensing&lt;/strong&gt; now applies to businesses with a turnover up to Rs 50 Crore, while &lt;strong&gt;Central Licensing&lt;/strong&gt; is mandatory for those exceeding Rs 50 Crore.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Perpetual Licences:&lt;/strong&gt; FSSAI has introduced &lt;strong&gt;lifetime validity&lt;/strong&gt; for licences, eliminating the need for periodic renewals.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Street Vendor Relief:&lt;/strong&gt; Vendors registered under the Street Vendors Act, 2014, will be &lt;strong&gt;automatically treated as registered&lt;/strong&gt; with FSSAI, benefiting over 10 lakh individuals.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Implementation:&lt;/strong&gt; These changes are set to take effect from &lt;strong&gt;1st April 2026&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;FSSAI (Food Safety and Standards Authority of India)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Established under the Food Safety and Standards Act, 2006, it is an autonomous body under the Ministry of Health &amp;amp; Family Welfare responsible for protecting public health through food regulation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Ease of Doing Business&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;By removing the renewal process, the government aims to reduce the &amp;quot;Inspector Raj&amp;quot; and compliance burden on micro and small-scale food operators.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chile.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jose Antonio Kast was officially sworn in as the President of Chile at the National Congress in Valparaiso.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Succession:&lt;/strong&gt; He succeeds &lt;strong&gt;Gabriel Boric&lt;/strong&gt; as the head of state.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Political Party:&lt;/strong&gt; Kast is the founder of the &lt;strong&gt;Republican Party&lt;/strong&gt; (established in 2019) and is known for his far-right political stance.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Election Victory:&lt;/strong&gt; He won the presidency in a runoff election held in December 2025, defeating the left-wing candidate &lt;strong&gt;Jeannette Jara&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Policy Stance:&lt;/strong&gt; His administration is expected to focus on &lt;strong&gt;tough security measures&lt;/strong&gt;, strict immigration control, and conservative social policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Chilean Presidency&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The President of Chile is both the head of state and head of government. The term of office is &lt;strong&gt;four years&lt;/strong&gt;, and immediate re-election is not permitted under the current constitution.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Krishi Sakhi Initiative.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Agriculture Insurance Company Of India Limited has launched the Krishi Sakhi Initiative to empower women farmers and foster inclusive growth within the agricultural sector.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Krishi Sakhi Initiative was officially launched by the Agriculture Insurance Company of India Limited to champion the cause of women in agriculture.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;The primary goal of the initiative is to foster inclusive economic growth and sustained development within the rural agricultural sector.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;The program aims to create continuous awareness regarding the critical role of women in agriculture through structured, month-wise activities and campaigns.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Krishi Sakhi Initiative&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Launched By - Agriculture Insurance Company Of India Limited&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Target Group - Women Farmers&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Core Objective - Empowerment and inclusive agricultural growth&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;International Year Of The Woman Farmer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Overview: The United Nations and the Food And Agriculture Organization have recognized the year 2026 as the International Year Of The Woman Farmer, aligning perfectly with this new Indian initiative.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Agriculture Insurance Company Of India Limited&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Overview: It is a leading public sector insurance company in India that primarily offers yield-based and weather-based crop insurance programs to protect farmers from financial losses.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Food And Agriculture Organization (FAO)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Overview: A specialized agency of the United Nations that leads international efforts to defeat hunger, improve nutrition, and promote sustainable agricultural practices worldwide.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bharat Mandapam.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ministry of Housing &amp;amp; Urban Affairs (MoHUA) hosted the AMRUT Mitra Mahotsav at Bharat Mandapam, New Delhi, to celebrate the role of women Self-Help Groups (SHGs) in water services.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Objective:&lt;/strong&gt; To honor &lt;strong&gt;AMRUT Mitras&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;mdash;women SHG members active in water quality testing, billing, and maintenance of urban water assets.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chairperson:&lt;/strong&gt; The event was chaired by Union Minister &lt;strong&gt;Shri Manohar Lal&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Current Reach:&lt;/strong&gt; Over &lt;strong&gt;45,000 women&lt;/strong&gt; are working as AMRUT Mitras across 1,910 cities in 34 States/UTs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expansion Plan:&lt;/strong&gt; The government aims to scale this model to &lt;strong&gt;5,000 cities&lt;/strong&gt; to ensure sustainable water governance.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Innovation:&lt;/strong&gt; A &lt;strong&gt;compendium of best practices&lt;/strong&gt; was launched to document successful case studies of women-led water management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;AMRUT 2.0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The second phase of the mission aims to make cities &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;water secure&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; through circular economy of water and focusing on functional water tap connections to all households.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Bharat Mandapam&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Located at Pragati Maidan, New Delhi, it is an International Exhibition-cum-Convention Centre (IECC) that rose to global fame as the venue for the 2023 G20 Summit.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reserve Bank of India.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) has won the prestigious &amp;#39;Global Initiative of the Year Award&amp;#39; for its pioneering .bank.in domain project.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Objective:&lt;/strong&gt; The transition to the &lt;strong&gt;.bank.in&lt;/strong&gt; domain is aimed at curbing &lt;strong&gt;cyber fraud&lt;/strong&gt;, specifically phishing and look-alike website scams.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Restricted Access:&lt;/strong&gt; Only &lt;strong&gt;RBI-regulated entities&lt;/strong&gt; are permitted to use this domain, providing an immediate layer of verification for customers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Implementation:&lt;/strong&gt; All licensed banks in India were mandated to migrate their net banking websites to this secure domain by &lt;strong&gt;October 31, 2025&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt; The project involved the Government of India, the &lt;strong&gt;National Internet Exchange of India (NIXI)&lt;/strong&gt;, and the &lt;strong&gt;IDRBT&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Central Banking Awards&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Central Banking Awards recognize excellence in the central banking community. The RBI has been a frequent recipient of various categories, reflecting its proactive stance on digital infrastructure and financial stability.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;208 Medals.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The India leg of the World Para Athletics Grand Prix 2026 concluded in New Delhi with the host nation securing the top position.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Medal Tally:&lt;/strong&gt; India finished at the top with a massive total of &lt;strong&gt;208 Medals&lt;/strong&gt; (75 Gold, 69 Silver, and 64 Bronze).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Global Standings:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Russia&lt;/strong&gt; secured the 2nd position with 35 medals, followed by &lt;strong&gt;Bosnia and Herzegovina&lt;/strong&gt; in 3rd place.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Indian Contingent:&lt;/strong&gt; The host nation fielded its largest-ever contingent, consisting of &lt;strong&gt;219 athletes&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Star Performer:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Preethi Pal&lt;/strong&gt;, a Paris 2024 Paralympics bronze medallist, won gold in the Women&amp;rsquo;s 200m T35-T37.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clean Sweeps:&lt;/strong&gt; India achieved podium sweeps (winning all three medals) in events such as Men&amp;rsquo;s Shot Put F57 and Men&amp;rsquo;s 800m T53-T54.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;World Para Athletics Grand Prix&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is an annual international series of meetings organized by &lt;strong&gt;World Para Athletics&lt;/strong&gt; (a subcommittee of the IPC) since 2013.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Purpose&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The series provides top-tier competition for athletes with physical disabilities outside of the 4-year Paralympic cycle.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rupnagar, Banda, Beed, Gomati, Katihar, Beawar, and Neemuch.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Bureau of Indian Standards (BIS) expanded the mandatory gold hallmarking to seven new districts starting March 2, 2026.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;New Districts:&lt;/strong&gt; The seven districts are &lt;strong&gt;Rupnagar&lt;/strong&gt; (Punjab), &lt;strong&gt;Banda&lt;/strong&gt; (UP), &lt;strong&gt;Beed&lt;/strong&gt; (Maharashtra), &lt;strong&gt;Gomati&lt;/strong&gt; (Tripura), &lt;strong&gt;Katihar&lt;/strong&gt; (Bihar), &lt;strong&gt;Beawar&lt;/strong&gt; (Rajasthan), and &lt;strong&gt;Neemuch&lt;/strong&gt; (MP).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Phase:&lt;/strong&gt; This addition marks the &lt;strong&gt;Sixth Phase&lt;/strong&gt; of the mandatory hallmarking rollout.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Total Coverage:&lt;/strong&gt; With these additions, the total number of districts under mandatory hallmarking has reached &lt;strong&gt;380&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HUID:&lt;/strong&gt; Since June 2021, more than &lt;strong&gt;60 Crore&lt;/strong&gt; items have been hallmarked with a Hallmark Unique Identification (HUID) number.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal:&lt;/strong&gt; The primary objective is to protect consumers against adulteration and ensure the purity of gold jewellery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;HUID (Hallmark Unique Identification)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is a 6-digit alphanumeric code given to every piece of jewellery at the time of hallmarking. It allows for the traceability of the item and ensures its authenticity.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;BIS (Bureau of Indian Standards)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is the National Standards Body of India working under the Ministry of Consumer Affairs, Food &amp;amp; Public Distribution.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3 Years.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Government of India has enacted the &amp;#39;Promotion and Regulation of Online Gaming Act, 2025&amp;#39; to prohibit all forms of online money games.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;First-Time Offense:&lt;/strong&gt; Operating or facilitating prohibited money games can lead to imprisonment of up to 3 years, a fine of up to ₹1 Crore, or both.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Repeat Offenses:&lt;/strong&gt; A second conviction carries a minimum of &lt;strong&gt;3 years&lt;/strong&gt; (extending to 5 years) and a minimum fine of &lt;strong&gt;₹1 Crore&lt;/strong&gt; (extending to ₹2 Crores).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advertising Penalties:&lt;/strong&gt; Promoting such games is punishable by up to &lt;strong&gt;2 years&lt;/strong&gt; of imprisonment or a fine of up to &lt;strong&gt;₹50 Lakhs&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scope:&lt;/strong&gt; The Act prohibits all online money games, regardless of whether they are Games of Skill or Games of Chance.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Regulatory Body:&lt;/strong&gt; The legislation establishes the Online Gaming Authority of India for national-level oversight.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Information Technology Act, 2000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The authorities are empowered to use provisions under the IT Act, 2000, to block access to unlawful digital platforms and ensure the enforcement of the Gaming Act.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
